This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with video frame inpainting, which is a common task in computer vision. The use of deep learning architectures and optical flow also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.MM) and Learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach for handling arbitrary input video size and length, which could fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. Finally, the paper also deals with preserving temporal consistency and spatial details, which could be relevant to the Graphics (cs.GR) category.
